<TEXT>
 a cold war spy case landed a cia employee and his wife in prison.
 he's still behind bars, but her story has a different ending.
 bob glascoff has details in today's edition of "headliners."
<TURN>
 october 1994, rosario ames is sentenced to five years in prison for helping her
 husband, cia turncoat aldrich ames, sell american secrets to the soviets.
 the colombia native met her future husband while working as a diplomat in
 mexico city.
 ames recruited her as an informant in 1983, then married her two years later.
 during that time, ames started passing information to moscow.
 the couple spent more than $1.5 million they received as payment on lavish
 jewelry, homes and cars.
 eventually, the cia caught on to their activities through electronic
 surveillance.
 aldrich ames admitted to espionage and tax evasion in order to get a more
 lenient sentence for his wife.
 she served four years of a five-year prison term.
 released two years ago, she has since returned to colombia with their son.
 with "headliners," i'm bob glascoff.
</TEXT>
